Class HISankey

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.highsoft.highcharts.Common.HIChartsClasses.HISeries
      • com.highsoft.highcharts.Common.HIChartsClasses.HISankey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HIChartsJSONSerializable

    public class HISankey
extends HISeries
    description: A sankey series. If the type option is not specified, it is inherited from chart.type. For options that apply to multiple series, it is recommended to add them to the plotOptions.series options structure. To apply to all series of this specific type, apply it to plotOptions. sankey.

    • Field Detail

      • curveFactor

        public java.lang.Number curveFactor
        description: Higher numbers makes the links in a sankey diagram render more curved. A curveFactor of 0 makes the lines straight. default: 0.33

      • colors

        public java.util.ArrayList<HIColor> colors
        description: A series specific or series type specific color set to apply instead of the global colors when colorByPoint is true.

      • linkOpacity

        public java.lang.Number linkOpacity
        description: Opacity for the links between nodes in the sankey diagram. default: 0.5

      • nodeWidth

        public java.lang.Number nodeWidth
        description: The pixel width of each node in a sankey diagram, or the height in case the chart is inverted. default: 20

      • colorByPoint

        public java.lang.Boolean colorByPoint
        description: When using automatic point colors pulled from the options.colors collection, this option determines whether the chart should receive one color per series or one color per point. demo: https://jsfiddle.net/gh/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/highcharts/plotoptions/column-colorbypoint-false/ : False by default https://jsfiddle.net/gh/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/highcharts/plotoptions/column-colorbypoint-true/ : True default: True

      • nodePadding

        public java.lang.Number nodePadding
        description: The padding between nodes in a sankey diagram, in pixels. default: 10

      • minPointLength

        public java.lang.Number minPointLength
        description: The minimal height for a column or width for a bar. By default, 0 values are not shown. To visualize a 0 (or close to zero) point, set the minimal point length to a pixel value like 3. In stacked column charts, minPointLength might not be respected for tightly packed values. demo: https://jsfiddle.net/gh/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/highcharts/plotoptions/column-minpointlength/ : Zero base value https://jsfiddle.net/gh/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/highcharts/plotoptions/column-minpointlength-pos-and-neg/ : Positive and negative close to zero values default: 0

      • nodes

        public java.util.ArrayList<HINodes> nodes
        description: A collection of options for the individual nodes. The nodes in a sankey diagram are auto-generated instances of Highcharts.Point, but options can be applied here and linked by the id. demo: https://jsfiddle.net/gh/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/highcharts/css/sankey/ : Sankey diagram with node options
